threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a statically linked ARMv7 ELF binary, characteristic of an advanced malware loader or dropper. It contains a sophisticated, custom-built ELF loader, indicated by functions that parse ELF headers, program headers, and dynamic sections (`sub_118c8`, `sub_13014`). This functionality allows it to manually load and execute other binaries. The binary is designed for embedded systems, as evidenced by its handling of the uClibc linker cache (`/etc/ld-uClibc.so.cache`). Furthermore, it attempts to run as a background process by redirecting I/O to `/dev/null`. This combination of a custom ELF loader and daemonization is highly indicative of malicious activity, likely to deploy a second-stage payload.
